description:
Grant Morrison. Paul Pope. Dave McKean. Bill Sienkiewicz. Farel Dalrymple. Yuko Shimizu. David Mack. Legendary artists through the ages have interpreted the timeless tale of Prometheus' gift of fire, creating a powerful visual tapestry that spans centuries. In this landmark collaboration between the Philadelphia Museum of Art and the Eisner-winning minds behind Little Nemo: Dream Another Dream, the torch has been passed to these visionary creators, who together explore the gift of creation and price of defiance.

  • Prometheus Bound (painting by Peter Paul Rubens & Frans Snyders)
  • Foreward (by Josh O'Neill)
  • Prometheus is Here! (by Grant Morrison & Farel Dalrymple)
  • Prometheus Unheard (by Dave McKean)
  • Challeging the Gods: Rubens Becoming Rubens (by Andrea Tsurumi)
  • Promtheus Untold (by David Mack)
  • The Gift of Fire (by Josh O'Neill & Lisk Feng)
  • The Messenger (pin-up by Paul Pope)
  • A Portrait of Prometheus Sans Titan (pin-up by Yuko Shimizu)
  • Foie Gras (by James Comey)

Front & back covers by Bill Sienkiewicz

After a lifetime of being manipulated by a succession of Masters, Andre Toulon's Puppets may have finally found a way out. Is the psychic Madam Adon the savior they have been looking for? And if so, what is the price of freedom? REBIRTH moves the Puppet Master universe in a bold new direction!

description: Follow the rise of the Bay Area's heaviest heavy metal band Exodus. From Kirk Hammett's involvement with the group to the crazy antics of Paul Baloff, Exodus is one of the most amazing live bands who's just now claiming the mantle of metal they've long deserved.

With great power comes a bit of insanity, anxiety, and a dash of social alienation! Have you ever fantasized about being a super hero? Well Dru Dragowski does; that's all this nineteen-year-old, comic book obsessed, high school senior thinks about. She needs to escape the normalcy of suburban life! Her plan? To become a real-life superhero by recreating the origins of her favorite comic characters! Hopefully then, she can become a hero not only for herself - but to protect everyone around her! If only that plan went just the slightest bit right... This fun, teen-agnst filled monthly series is created by the sensational writing duo that brings you Harley Quinn and Starfire - Jimmy Palmiotti & Amanda Conner.

Can the Doctor stop the Time War from happening all over again?
